<header>
	<img class="rightFloat" src="../media/TT_WT2b.jpg" mode="16" id="1004"  />
		
		Read this sample answer to the writing task in the previous exercise and find the mistakes. There are 15. Click on them.
		
		Writing Task 2
</header>
	
<section id="body">
  <img class="rightFloat" src="../media/TT_AW_015.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"/>
  <br/>
  <ol id="questionList"/>
</section>

<section id="fb1">
  <p align="left">
    <b>However -&gt; Although</b>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb2">
  <p align="left">
    <b>oppose -&gt; disagree</b>
    <font color="#0000ff"/>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb3">
  <p align="left">
    <b>On the contrast -&gt; On the contrary</b>
    <font color="#0000ff"/>
  </p>
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">We say 'in contrast' and 'on the contrary'. However, they do not mean the same thing!</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb4">
  <p align="left">
    <b>I am in favour of -&gt; I am convinced that</b>
    <font color="#0000ff"/>
  </p>
  <p align="left">'in favour of' needs to be followed by a gerund or noun.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb5">
  <p align="left">
    <b>Another -&gt; The most important</b>
    <font color="#0000ff"/>
  </p>
  <p align="left">This is the first reason mentioned by the writer.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb6">
  <p align="left">
    <b>on the other hand -&gt; in turn</b>
    <font color="#0000ff"/>
  </p>
  <p align="left">The writer is adding another comment supporting the previous idea.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb7">
  <p align="left">
    <b>The main reason -&gt; The second reason</b>
    <font color="#0000ff"/>
  </p>
  <p align="left">The 'main' reason has already been discussed in the first paragraph.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb8">
  <p align="left">
    <b>as -&gt; such as</b>
    <font color="#0000ff"/>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb9">
  <p align="left">
    <b>including -&gt; for instance</b>
    <font color="#0000ff"/>
  </p>
  <p align="left">'including' should come before the example is given, not after it i.e. 'including food suppliers'.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb10">
  <p align="left">
    <b>A final reason -&gt; A further reason</b>
    <font color="#0000ff"/>
  </p>
  <p align="left">This is not the writer's final argument.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb11">
  <p align="left">
    <b>A second reason -&gt; A final reason</b>
    <font color="#0000ff"/>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb12">
  <p align="left">
    <b>against -&gt; in favour of</b>
    <font color="#0000ff"/>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb13">
  <p align="left">
    <b>For example -&gt; Consequently</b>
    <font color="#0000ff"/>
  </p>
  <p align="left">This means 'as a result'.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb14">
  <p align="left">
    <b>In contrast -&gt; Likewise</b>
    <font color="#0000ff"/>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb15">
  <p align="left">
    <b>support -&gt; believe</b>
    <font color="#0000ff"/>
  </p>
  <p align="left">'support' needs to be followed by a noun or gerund.</p>
</section>

